a full tank of Nostalgia Max

17:01.791 --> 17:05.166
mixed with banned '80s products
full of dangerous chemicals.

17:05.250 --> 17:07.166
What could go wrong?

17:11.000 --> 17:12.583
Did I do that?

17:13.083 --> 17:15.666
Yes! Yes, I did!

17:17.083 --> 17:19.000
-Okay, this is it.

17:19.083 --> 17:21.250
Vietcong stronghold.

17:23.916 --> 17:26.166
Damn it. This was Myc's last location.

17:26.250 --> 17:27.666
He must have left tracks.

17:27.750 --> 17:29.958
Man, maybe I was too harsh on Brett.

17:30.041 --> 17:32.166
I just don't get why he's so obsessed
with this decade.

17:32.250 --> 17:34.166
He is clearly going through something.

17:34.250 --> 17:37.708
He said he wanted to be
streamed back to his childhood.

17:37.791 --> 17:41.125
I've known POWs
with a better grip on reality.

17:41.208 --> 17:44.166
I thought it was another one
of his weird '80s references.

17:44.250 --> 17:47.083
-I mean, what the hell is a Koosh ball?
-How would you know?

17:47.166 --> 17:49.000
You've never watched
anything from the '80s.

17:49.083 --> 17:52.250
And it's not about what a Koosh is.
It's what a Koosh means.

17:52.333 --> 17:53.375
How do I make it up to him?

17:53.458 --> 17:54.875
Like most white dudes,

17:54.958 --> 17:57.666
the only way to bond with Brett
is to watch '80s movies

17:57.750 --> 18:00.458
then quote them
instead of thinking of jokes yourself.

18:00.541 --> 18:02.291
-Go. We'll keep looking.

18:02.375 --> 18:05.750
And if I see one goddamn rewind fee…

18:05.833 --> 18:08.708
-Thanks, Glenn.
-They grow up so fast.

18:09.916 --> 18:11.666
Good evening, ma'am.
It's Super Saver Night.

18:11.750 --> 18:13.416
-What do you want to see?
-Everything.

18:13.500 --> 18:15.458
I wanna super save my friendship.

18:16.625 --> 18:18.625
Listen, I don't need to know
your whole deal.

18:30.458 --> 18:33.416
Okay, I memorized
your whole must-see list,

18:33.500 --> 18:36.958
but I still don't get why Brett
is so wrapped up in this stuff.

18:38.208 --> 18:41.291
-I'm sorry I went in your room, Mitch.

18:41.375 --> 18:43.750
I just wanted to be like my big brother.

18:43.833 --> 18:45.625
You're my hero, Mitch.

18:45.708 --> 18:47.083
Aw!

18:47.166 --> 18:49.708
The hell? That family looks just like--

18:49.791 --> 18:53.166
The Weavers. The heartwarming family
from TV's The Growing Years.

18:53.250 --> 18:55.000
Yeah, meat and loaf.

18:55.083 --> 18:58.625
Oh my God. That family in the hologram
wasn't his family.

18:58.708 --> 19:01.041
It was this '80s sitcom family.

19:01.125 --> 19:02.833
I'm not sure who we're talking about.

19:02.916 --> 19:04.500
Yeah, welcome to my fucking world.

19:08.416 --> 19:10.833
Don't you forget about me.

19:10.916 --> 19:13.166
Where is my Brett Pack?

19:14.208 --> 19:15.250
Faster.

19:15.333 --> 19:18.416
I thought you kids were hopped up
on milk hormones and grape juice.

19:18.500 --> 19:20.666
I'm pedaling as fast as I can.

19:20.750 --> 19:23.500
Seriously?
No wonder your dad left.

19:23.583 --> 19:25.041
-That's it!

19:25.125 --> 19:26.791
-Fuck you, Myc!

19:26.875 --> 19:30.416
-Shit!

19:30.500 --> 19:32.500
You ruined the magic of childhood.

19:32.583 --> 19:35.541
I hope you get mutilated
by the government, asshole!

19:35.625 --> 19:38.750
Oh, the signal's back.
It's coming toward us really quickly.

19:38.833 --> 19:40.875
It's like he's right on top of us.

19:43.750 --> 19:44.875
Found him.

19:44.958 --> 19:47.000
I remember everything.

19:47.083 --> 19:48.666
It's you guys.

19:48.750 --> 19:50.625
I hate you guys.

19:50.708 --> 19:52.208
Wait, there's one missing.

19:52.291 --> 19:54.000
-Oh my God. Brett!

19:54.083 --> 19:55.416
Yeah, Brett.

19:55.500 --> 19:58.500
That big, dumb pussy
with all the Mormon energy.

19:59.458 --> 20:01.666
He's floating right behind me, isn't he?

20:01.750 --> 20:02.958
Oh my God! Oh shit!

20:03.041 --> 20:05.416
I am
the mighty Nostalgia Max!

20:05.500 --> 20:08.708
Bow before my totally tubular power!

20:08.791 --> 20:11.500
-It's the chemtrails!
-He must have gotten an overdose.

20:11.583 --> 20:14.291
He's turned
into some kind of nostalgia monster!

20:14.375 --> 20:16.916
I'm Lester Majors live in Town Square.

20:17.000 --> 20:17.833
-Ow!

20:17.916 --> 20:20.083
Oh no, you don't, Lester.
This is my scoop.

20:20.166 --> 20:24.000
Pandemonium tonight as some kind
of nostalgia monster attacks Town Square.

20:24.083 --> 20:26.000
Are your children going to die?

20:26.083 --> 20:28.291
If you change that channel,
they just might.

20:28.375 --> 20:31.333
Brett, float down here right this second.

20:31.416 --> 20:33.916
Wha'choo talkin' 'bout, Glennis?

20:35.375 --> 20:37.625
Where's the beef?
Where's the beef?

20:37.708 --> 20:39.500
-Where's the beef?
-Don't let him spray you.

20:39.583 --> 20:42.250
You'll become a stunted man-child
like Chris Hardwick!

20:42.333 --> 20:45.833
-Oh God.
-We're staying in the '80s forever!

20:45.916 --> 20:48.000
It will be radical!

20:51.791 --> 20:54.500
Say hello to my little friends.

20:54.583 --> 20:56.166
-Don't let them leave.

20:56.791 --> 20:58.625
-Holy shit!

20:58.708 --> 21:00.708
-The cow says die!

21:00.791 --> 21:02.333
Pull me up, pull me up!

21:02.416 --> 21:05.166
Oh God!
It's Ready Player One all over again!

21:09.416 --> 21:12.458
Brett, what's with
your whole Firestarter, Slimer vibe?

21:12.541 --> 21:14.041
It's a little derivative.

21:14.125 --> 21:16.291
How much time
did you spend at Blockbuster?

21:16.375 --> 21:17.708
Enough to make this.

21:33.916 --> 21:36.125
I didn't know violence could end badly.

21:36.208 --> 21:37.833
Tragic, dead at 40.

21:37.916 --> 21:39.083
Hey, fuck you.

21:44.166 --> 21:47.833
Brett, listen.
I know why you're doing this.

21:47.916 --> 21:49.166
I get it now.

21:49.250 --> 21:51.291
All this junk was important to you

21:51.375 --> 21:55.916
because you were using a fake family
to make up for your crappy one.

21:56.000 --> 21:57.083
Am I right?

21:57.166 --> 22:00.208
I… I…

22:00.791 --> 22:04.250
Fight it, Brett.
Think of your real family.

22:06.541 --> 22:09.041
Family photo. Everybody crowd in, come on.

22:12.833 --> 22:15.125
My kids, they're champions.

22:15.208 --> 22:17.625
-Except for Brett.
-Which one's Brett?

22:19.750 --> 22:22.166
Master Brett, your parents called.

22:22.250 --> 22:25.958
They'll be extending their trip
to Barbados one more week.

22:26.041 --> 22:28.041
But tomorrow's my birthday.

22:28.125 --> 22:29.291
Indeed.

22:30.208 --> 22:31.291
Are my brothers coming?

22:31.375 --> 22:35.916
They send their best from military school
and rehab, respectively.

22:36.000 --> 22:37.625
Will there be anything else?

22:37.708 --> 22:39.166
No, I'm okay.

22:39.250 --> 22:40.708
You're my hero, Mitch.

22:40.791 --> 22:42.625
Aw!

22:46.208 --> 22:48.375
I just want…

22:48.875 --> 22:51.041
Wanted a… a loving family.

22:51.125 --> 22:54.208
Hey, I get it, man.
My family was dogshit too.

22:54.791 --> 22:58.916
But you don't need a fake family
when you've got real BFFs.

22:59.000 --> 23:01.791
-My BFFs?

23:01.875 --> 23:03.958
We're your business family forever.

23:10.333 --> 23:12.625
-Yeah, all right!

23:13.875 --> 23:16.333
This just in,
all the white people are hugging.

23:16.416 --> 23:18.250
It really is the fucking '80s.

23:18.833 --> 23:21.500
Whoa, I really got hit hard
with nostalgia.

23:21.583 --> 23:22.708
I'm so sorry, guys.

23:22.791 --> 23:25.791
I guess I got carried away
by this fake '80s town.

23:25.875 --> 23:28.291
But I'm ready
to go back to the 2020s.

23:28.375 --> 23:30.666
Wait a minute. Fake '80s town?

23:30.750 --> 23:33.500
-And what did you mean by 2020s?

23:33.583 --> 23:35.291
Are you from the future?

23:35.375 --> 23:37.750
Uh, yes, let's go with that.

23:37.833 --> 23:42.083
-We'll see you guys in 30-something years.
-Wait, can we use your time machine?

23:42.166 --> 23:47.208
We want to go back
to the one perfect decade, the 1950s.

23:47.291 --> 23:50.041
-Huh. I guess everybody's nostalgic

23:50.125 --> 23:52.208
for a simpler time
that never really existed.

23:52.291 --> 23:56.458
And the word "Chinese"
just meant "generally Asian."

23:56.541 --> 23:58.166
I really fucking hate this town.

23:58.250 --> 24:00.291
-Goddamn it!

24:02.166 --> 24:03.333
Oh hey, virgins.

24:03.416 --> 24:05.916
Kevin, Charlie, fat kid, Tyrone.

24:06.000 --> 24:06.833
Man, come on.

24:06.916 --> 24:09.083
I guess you'll be going back
to your home planet.

24:09.166 --> 24:11.500
It's actually
a brownstone in Alexandria.

24:11.583 --> 24:12.750
But don't worry, Kevin.

24:12.833 --> 24:17.666
-I'll be right here.

24:17.750 --> 24:20.375
That's for throwing me off a cliff,
you little bastard.

24:20.458 --> 24:22.333
You know, Brett,
you weren't totally wrong.

24:22.416 --> 24:25.416
This decade did bring us
accidentally closer together.

24:25.500 --> 24:27.666
Hey, I've got an idea
for when we get back.

24:29.250 --> 24:32.208
-Family dinner. What are we watching?
-Boom.

24:32.291 --> 24:35.041
Can you believe Goonies was only 6.99?

24:35.125 --> 24:36.375
Thoroughly, yes.

24:36.458 --> 24:38.125
Ah.

24:38.208 --> 24:40.250
-Everything you remember?

24:40.333 --> 24:41.375
Even better.

24:43.750 --> 24:47.625
So is their disabled brother
just straight up chained to a wall?

24:47.708 --> 24:49.541
Huh. Wow, yeah, that's…

24:49.625 --> 24:51.291
